01:05.290 --> 01:07.248
It was my father's
religious beliefs

01:07.250 --> 01:09.288
that destroyed
our family.

03:01.125 --> 03:04.875
We have to be so very
careful what we believe in.

03:07.332 --> 03:09.248
Hello.

03:09.250 --> 03:13.288
There's a... there's a little
lad coming through to me now.

03:13.290 --> 03:15.250
Come on, come on.

03:16.665 --> 03:19.705
He wants to talk
to someone.

03:19.707 --> 03:22.705
Oh, he's a little...
he's a little lad

03:22.707 --> 03:25.830
and he... and he's
lookin' for his mom.

03:25.832 --> 03:29.538
He's sayin' his name
is... is Rob or Robbie.

03:29.540 --> 03:31.373
Is that... Is that you,
sweetheart?

03:31.375 --> 03:34.455
Stand up, my love.

03:34.457 --> 03:37.498
Mark Van Rhys is one of the
UK's most popular psychics.

03:37.500 --> 03:40.913
He believes that we're making a
documentary about his special powers

03:40.915 --> 03:45.123
whereas, in fact, we are investigating
the many, many complaints

03:45.125 --> 03:46.330
that have been made
against him.

03:46.332 --> 03:48.330
Do what this lady has done

03:48.332 --> 03:51.373
and accept the message.

03:51.375 --> 03:54.163
Mark?
Mark, can you hear me?

03:54.165 --> 03:55.705
Oh, just give us a sign.

03:55.707 --> 03:57.873
Scratch your nose
for a sec, see.

03:57.875 --> 03:59.373
Oh, thank God for that.

03:59.375 --> 04:02.038
It's Steph, right?
The woman's name's Steph.

04:02.040 --> 04:04.455
He calls you mom, but
he's... he's telling me

04:04.457 --> 04:06.205
your name is Steph?

04:06.207 --> 04:07.580
Oh, my God.

04:07.582 --> 04:08.748
Is... Is that right,
my love?

04:08.750 --> 04:10.498
- Are you Steph?
- Yeah.

04:10.500 --> 04:11.955
Okay,
so before the show starts

04:11.957 --> 04:13.788
Van Rhys' team
have audience members

04:13.790 --> 04:16.122
fill out one of these
prayer cards.

04:16.124 --> 04:18.413
There are the name
and details

04:18.415 --> 04:19.956
of the person
they wish to contact

04:19.958 --> 04:22.788
who has passed over
to the other side.

04:22.790 --> 04:25.623
The team then steal
this information

04:25.625 --> 04:27.456
and they feed it back
to Van Rhys

04:27.458 --> 04:30.373
through a hidden earpiece,
which I just hacked into

04:30.375 --> 04:32.831
and, hey, presto,
he's psychic.

04:36.458 --> 04:39.123
My blood hurts, mommy.

04:39.125 --> 04:41.083
My blood hurts.

04:42.375 --> 04:43.788
Why is he saying that?

04:43.790 --> 04:45.663
He had leukemia.

04:45.665 --> 04:47.081
Poor little lamb.

04:47.083 --> 04:50.663
Oh, he's got a cheeky
little smile, hasn't he?

04:50.665 --> 04:52.498
Yes.

04:52.500 --> 04:54.413
Children often make
the best connection

04:54.415 --> 04:57.373
because they're so pure,
you see.

04:57.375 --> 04:58.413
He was such a good boy.

04:58.415 --> 05:01.663
He still is, my sweet,
he still is.

05:01.665 --> 05:03.373
He says he's happy

05:03.375 --> 05:05.373
but he does miss
your cooking.

05:05.375 --> 05:07.248
Ladies and gentlemen,
I am sorry to interrupt.

05:07.250 --> 05:08.456
My name is
Professor Philip Goodman

05:08.458 --> 05:11.456
from the TV program
"Psychic Cheats."

05:11.458 --> 05:13.081
Mr. Van Rhys,
we have got..

05:13.083 --> 05:14.873
Mr. Van Rhys,
we have got proof

05:14.875 --> 05:17.498
that you are being fed information
through a hidden earpiece

05:17.500 --> 05:18.998
and you are passing it off
as contact with the dead...

05:19.000 --> 05:20.413
- Excuse me, sir.
- I beg your pardon.

05:20.415 --> 05:23.206
This is gonna be broadcast
on national television.

05:23.208 --> 05:25.163
Can you deny that you
were using an earpiece?

05:25.165 --> 05:26.456
That's slander.

05:26.458 --> 05:27.538
I can assure you,
you will be hearing

05:27.540 --> 05:28.998
from my solicitor
in due course.

05:29.000 --> 05:30.373
His assistant just
told him that Robbie

05:30.375 --> 05:32.456
was in
Christchurch Hospital.

05:32.458 --> 05:33.748
I can play you the tape.

05:33.750 --> 05:37.331
I'm sorry.
Christchurch Hospital!

05:37.333 --> 05:39.373
He's lyin', isn't he?

05:43.458 --> 05:45.623
The idea of us
and our loved ones dying

05:45.625 --> 05:49.248
just ceasing to exist
is so awful

05:49.250 --> 05:51.581
that we'll believe
anything which gives us hope

05:51.583 --> 05:54.456
that there might be
something beyond.

05:54.458 --> 05:57.663
That fear is known
as existential terror

05:57.665 --> 06:01.540
and the man who coined that phrase was Dr.
Charles Cameron.

06:05.583 --> 06:07.038
So why do you think

06:07.040 --> 06:09.913
the voices
come through you, Jean?

06:09.915 --> 06:11.457
'Cause we love her.

06:12.750 --> 06:15.623
And how many voices
are there?

06:15.625 --> 06:17.540
300.

06:19.250 --> 06:22.206
I moved back in.
I thought it would help.

06:22.208 --> 06:24.748
She's only here 'cause
she ran out of booze.

06:24.750 --> 06:25.748
Mom.

06:25.750 --> 06:28.498
She fingered herself
last night

06:28.500 --> 06:31.748
thinkin'
about John Travolta.

06:31.750 --> 06:34.373
Daddy sees everything.

06:34.375 --> 06:36.373
Jesus!

06:36.375 --> 06:38.081
I've seen this before.

06:38.083 --> 06:40.748
Your mother
feels abandoned

06:40.750 --> 06:42.748
at the death
of your father.

06:42.750 --> 06:43.998
Is she possessed?

06:44.000 --> 06:47.663
No, she's angry that
her husband had died.

06:47.665 --> 06:48.998
As for the vase..

06:51.000 --> 06:52.706
...I did that.

06:52.708 --> 06:56.413
The brain sees
what it wants to see.

06:56.415 --> 06:58.663
When I saw that clip
when I was a boy

06:58.665 --> 07:02.331
it was like
a lightning bolt struck me

07:02.333 --> 07:04.206
'cause it was like
somebody saying

07:04.208 --> 07:07.663
you don't have to have your life
ruled by superstitious fear.

07:07.665 --> 07:10.373
And the way that I'd been
brought up, that was..

07:10.375 --> 07:12.663
Honestly, that was a revelation
'cause I didn't realize

07:12.665 --> 07:14.706
there was a different way
of thinking.

07:14.708 --> 07:17.913
And, uh, from that minute

07:17.915 --> 07:20.163
I... I can remember thinking
that's what I wanna do

07:20.165 --> 07:23.038
that's what I wanna be,
that's who I want to be.

07:23.040 --> 07:24.663
The search
for the missing scientist

07:24.665 --> 07:27.788
and paranormalist, Charles
Cameron, has been called off

07:27.790 --> 07:30.623
three weeks after Mr. Cameron's
car was found abandoned

07:30.625 --> 07:32.456
near his house in Filey.

07:32.458 --> 07:34.663
I think it's ironic
to say the least

07:34.665 --> 07:36.163
that a man
who spent a lifetime

07:36.165 --> 07:39.331
explaining away mysteries
became one himself.

07:39.333 --> 07:41.875
I just wish I could
have met him is all.

09:00.332 --> 09:02.248
Hello, Professor Goodman.

09:02.250 --> 09:04.916
This is Charles Cameron.

09:06.750 --> 09:10.041
I'm sure you're surprised
to hear my voice.

09:11.832 --> 09:16.330
I'm familiar with your work
and I need to see you.

09:16.332 --> 09:18.664
I don't have long.

09:18.666 --> 09:23.039
Please come
to 79 East Shore

09:23.041 --> 09:25.705
Caravan Park..

09:54.875 --> 09:56.789
Hi, Mr. Cameron.
I'm Philip Goodman.

09:56.791 --> 09:58.123
Hello,
I'm Philip Goodman.

09:58.125 --> 09:59.289
Come on.

09:59.291 --> 10:00.748
Hello, Mr. Cameron,
I'm Philip Goodman.

10:00.750 --> 10:01.955
Hello, Charles.

10:01.957 --> 10:03.790
Hello,
I'm Philip Goodman.

10:23.166 --> 10:24.580
Hold on.

10:28.875 --> 10:30.498
Come in.

10:30.500 --> 10:32.457
I'm not paying
to heat the street.

10:45.457 --> 10:47.789
Oh, Jesus.

10:47.791 --> 10:50.705
Come in, sit down.
Sit down, please.

10:50.707 --> 10:52.123
Hello,
I'm Philip Goodman.

10:52.125 --> 10:54.125
I know who you are.

10:56.832 --> 10:58.498
I can't quite
believe this.

10:58.500 --> 11:01.205
No? Why is that?

11:01.207 --> 11:02.873
I think like everybody
else, I just pre..

11:02.875 --> 11:04.455
...sort of presumed
you were dead.

11:04.457 --> 11:07.790
How do you know I'm not?

11:18.500 --> 11:20.164
Can I ask what,
where you've been?

11:20.166 --> 11:22.705
- What's happened?
- Pour me a drink then.

11:22.707 --> 11:23.748
Pour it
from that bottle there.

11:23.750 --> 11:25.455
Bottle there. Pour it!

11:25.457 --> 11:26.790
Okay.

11:39.416 --> 11:40.958
I brought you something.

11:43.916 --> 11:45.833
It's a copy
of my latest book.

11:46.957 --> 11:49.750
- I signed it...
- Aah.

11:51.666 --> 11:52.833
Just stick it there.

11:54.832 --> 11:56.748
I'm so familiar
with your books

11:56.750 --> 11:59.955
and your, your TV work.

11:59.957 --> 12:01.830
I've always felt
a closeness to you.

12:01.832 --> 12:06.580
Save those sentiments
for your wife and family.

12:06.582 --> 12:09.707
What a surprise.
You're not married.

12:12.041 --> 12:13.830
You could always see
the truth, couldn't you?

12:13.832 --> 12:15.080
Truth?

12:15.082 --> 12:17.873
I look back now at my work

12:17.875 --> 12:21.873
with absolute shame.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.955
I see the arrogance
and the disrespect

12:23.957 --> 12:25.998
with which I went
into those homes.

12:26.000 --> 12:28.623
I took pleasure
in pulling those stories

12:28.625 --> 12:29.914
those people apart.

12:29.916 --> 12:31.414
I think you're being
really hard on yourself.

12:31.416 --> 12:35.580
I have seen your work,
Goodman.

12:35.582 --> 12:37.915
You want to know
what I think of it?

12:39.582 --> 12:41.955
It's shit.

12:41.957 --> 12:46.998
You are a conceited,
weak-willed coward.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.330
Editing out
any inconvenient data.

12:48.332 --> 12:49.955
Terrified of anything
that doesn't fit

12:49.957 --> 12:51.664
into your tiny
worldview...

12:51.666 --> 12:53.873
Okay, I'm done. I came here
in good faith because you...

12:53.875 --> 12:55.039
Three cases!

12:55.041 --> 12:57.498
I couldn't explain
three cases

12:57.500 --> 12:59.330
that haunt me still.

12:59.332 --> 13:01.373
Now you go and
investigate if you dare

13:01.375 --> 13:03.705
and come back and tell me
that I am wrong

13:03.707 --> 13:06.039
because I've come to one
inescapable conclusion

13:06.041 --> 13:07.873
and that is
the supernatural

13:07.875 --> 13:10.789
the unseen forces
that surround us

13:10.791 --> 13:12.580
everything that you and I
have spent a lifetime

13:12.582 --> 13:15.875
trying to debunk and
disprove, it's all true.

13:18.000 --> 13:19.832
Every last bit of it.

13:21.582 --> 13:24.914
Please, Mr. Goodman

13:24.916 --> 13:26.830
I'm begging you.

13:26.832 --> 13:29.165
Tell me I am wrong.

13:30.375 --> 13:33.500
I need you to tell me..

13:34.707 --> 13:35.915
...I'm wrong.

15:44.707 --> 15:46.665
Oh, hello, Tony?

15:48.041 --> 15:50.039
Aye, captain.

15:50.041 --> 15:51.998
Hello there.

15:52.000 --> 15:53.123
Hi, I'm Philip Goodman.

15:53.125 --> 15:55.789
Bang! Whoa! Slow.

15:55.791 --> 15:57.166
Too slow.

15:58.082 --> 15:59.955
Yeah, you look
like a teacher.

15:59.957 --> 16:01.498
Do I? Right.

16:01.500 --> 16:04.623
Um, well, technically,
I'm a professor.

16:04.625 --> 16:07.164
They bloody insist
on calling me that

16:07.166 --> 16:10.083
on that TV show that I do,
"Psychic Cheats."

16:11.416 --> 16:14.580
Oh, yeah, that's where
I know you from.

16:14.582 --> 16:17.205
- Yeah.
- Yeah, I seen that.

16:17.207 --> 16:18.582
Yeah, it's shit.

16:20.166 --> 16:22.123
I'm only joking
with you, mate.

16:22.125 --> 16:23.705
I ain't seen it.

16:23.707 --> 16:25.875
I have never even
heard of it, sunbeam.

16:28.375 --> 16:31.248
- Professor, eh?
- Yeah.

16:31.250 --> 16:32.955
You know,
that's the official title

16:32.957 --> 16:34.330
for someone who does
a "Punch And Judy."

16:34.332 --> 16:36.248
I bet you didn't know
that, did you?

16:36.250 --> 16:38.123
- No, I didn't actually.
- There you go then.

16:38.125 --> 16:40.039
The professor
just learned something

16:40.041 --> 16:42.080
from the humble
night watchman.

16:42.082 --> 16:43.414
And that's what you do,
is it?

16:45.957 --> 16:47.707
You're a night watchman?

16:49.207 --> 16:52.123
Actually, I don't wanna
talk about it, mate.

16:52.125 --> 16:53.330
Sorry?

16:53.332 --> 16:55.290
I'm just not feeling
very chatty, sunbeam.

17:01.707 --> 17:03.250
For fuck's sake.

17:08.583 --> 17:11.247
Oh, did I forget to mention
that there was a fee?

17:11.249 --> 17:13.163
- 100 quid.
- 50.

17:13.165 --> 17:14.165
Done.

17:18.958 --> 17:23.083
20, 25..

17:26.833 --> 17:28.165
50.

17:35.290 --> 17:36.163
So that's what
you do, yeah?

17:36.165 --> 17:37.873
You're a night watchman?

17:37.875 --> 17:41.081
Well, I was, you know,
when, um, it happened.

17:41.083 --> 17:43.291
- And now?
- Now?

17:45.040 --> 17:46.331
Let's just say
that immigration

17:46.333 --> 17:48.250
has made things
a bit tough, yeah?

17:53.375 --> 17:56.125
How about family?
You married?

17:57.250 --> 17:59.248
I was married
for 15 years.

17:59.250 --> 18:01.248
You get less for murder,
don't you?

18:03.333 --> 18:05.206
Did you divorce?

18:05.208 --> 18:07.583
She died 23 years ago.

18:08.375 --> 18:10.706
I'm sorry.

18:10.708 --> 18:13.581
If she fell ill now,
they'd smash that cancer.

18:13.583 --> 18:16.038
Different world, isn't it?

18:16.040 --> 18:19.038
Yeah. Any children?

18:19.040 --> 18:21.207
Mind your own
fucking business.

18:23.540 --> 18:25.538
How many more of these questions
have you got, eh, Kojak?

18:25.540 --> 18:27.500
It's worse than getting
car insurance, this.

18:50.708 --> 18:53.083
I got a daughter, Marnie.

18:54.875 --> 18:57.873
I was always
a big Hitchcock fan.

18:57.875 --> 19:00.788
If I had had a boy,
I would've called him Norman.

19:00.790 --> 19:03.498
- How old is she?
- She's 30.

19:03.500 --> 19:07.373
Right, so she was seven
when your wife died.

19:07.375 --> 19:09.165
That must have been tough.

19:10.500 --> 19:12.913
Marnie is not my wife's.

19:12.915 --> 19:14.373
I had a little bit
on the side.

19:14.375 --> 19:15.915
What are you gonna do, eh?

19:17.083 --> 19:19.956
Right.
You see much of her?

19:19.958 --> 19:21.373
Well, I'm done here.
This is bullshit.

19:21.375 --> 19:23.581
I thought you wanted to
talk about what I'd seen.

19:23.583 --> 19:25.375
Tony, I'm just
trying to help.

19:26.540 --> 19:28.500
You can't help me, mate.

19:43.083 --> 19:44.541
She's in hospital.

19:46.000 --> 19:47.748
She's been in there
five years.

19:47.750 --> 19:50.081
Oh, fuck.

19:50.083 --> 19:52.208
Locked-in syndrome
they call it.

19:53.915 --> 19:56.456
Her eyes are open, but..

19:56.458 --> 19:59.250
...everything else
is paralyzed.

20:03.165 --> 20:05.081
If I go and see her,
I... I don't know

20:05.083 --> 20:07.041
if she even knows
if I'm there or not.

20:10.040 --> 20:11.832
I stopped going
in the end.

20:13.250 --> 20:15.208
I couldn't handle it.

20:17.375 --> 20:18.750
My little girl.

20:19.833 --> 20:22.123
I'm sorry.

20:22.125 --> 20:23.915
You apologize a lot,
don't you?

20:25.415 --> 20:27.000
Guilty conscience?

20:30.665 --> 20:32.082
You wanna..

20:33.500 --> 20:35.458
Wanna tell me
about your incident?

20:36.540 --> 20:38.831
You'll think I'm mad.

20:38.833 --> 20:41.250
Everyone else does.
Even my priest.

20:43.875 --> 20:45.833
Ah, you don't believe,
do you?

20:56.540 --> 20:58.875
It was my last night
working that job.

21:00.790 --> 21:02.538
Quarter to 4:00
in the morning.

21:02.540 --> 21:04.500
That is a shit time
of night.

21:05.458 --> 21:07.413
Even after seven years
of doin' that shift

21:07.415 --> 21:09.500
your body never
gets used to it.

21:11.040 --> 21:13.248
That place had a history.

21:13.250 --> 21:15.208
None of it was nice.

21:16.375 --> 21:19.331
Hundreds of years before,
it was, um, it was a..

21:19.333 --> 21:22.041
What do you call it?
A nuthouse for women.

21:23.500 --> 21:25.123
Mad birds roaming
about the place.

21:25.125 --> 21:27.456
Old brasses, drunks

21:27.458 --> 21:29.998
young girls that got
themselves knocked up

21:30.000 --> 21:33.333
newborns that no one
wanted, thrown away.

21:35.665 --> 21:36.832
Miserable.

21:37.958 --> 21:41.163
In the month
leadin' up to that night

21:41.165 --> 21:43.663
two of the new
foreign blokes quit.

21:43.665 --> 21:45.625
They said
they had seen things.

21:47.040 --> 21:48.875
Did you believe them?

21:50.333 --> 21:53.000
I wish I had.
Christ Almighty.

22:35.500 --> 22:37.665
Hello? Marek?

22:40.125 --> 22:42.500
You have to press
the button on the side.

22:46.458 --> 22:51.708
Press the big black button on
the side, you Russian prick.

22:53.915 --> 22:57.163
Yo, Tony.
I am in other building.

22:57.165 --> 23:00.332
Congratulations.
Which other building?

23:01.665 --> 23:05.081
Um, the building
with the blue door.

23:05.083 --> 23:09.288
Alright. You're in
building number three.

23:09.290 --> 23:12.538
Yes, yes, yes.
What do I do?

23:12.540 --> 23:15.582
Well, you sit on your arse
for the next 10 hours.

23:16.625 --> 23:18.788
Every hour
go for a walk round

23:18.790 --> 23:20.663
and then chart it.

23:20.665 --> 23:23.538
Set that timer
that I gave ya.

23:23.540 --> 23:25.663
Other than that,
you do what you want.

23:25.665 --> 23:29.165
I don't know, read,
play chess, learn English.

23:31.458 --> 23:34.248
Okay.
Thank you a lot, Tony.

23:34.250 --> 23:36.040
Alright, Marek.
No worries.

23:45.708 --> 23:48.038
And then she sat down
with a cup of tea

23:48.040 --> 23:49.873
and just went mad.

23:49.875 --> 23:51.456
"That's typical of you,"
she said.

23:51.458 --> 23:53.913
"Lord Muck, always
thinkin' of himself.

23:53.915 --> 23:56.498
"Didn't even cross his mind
to ask if I wanted one, so.."

23:56.500 --> 23:59.663
I'm havin'
a cup of tea, mate.

23:59.665 --> 24:00.956
What do you reckon?

24:00.958 --> 24:04.538
Was I selfish?
Is that what marriage is?

24:04.540 --> 24:07.081
A lifetime sentence
of making

24:07.083 --> 24:09.498
two cups of tea
instead of one?

24:09.500 --> 24:13.581
Or is it good to grab
a bit of healthy me time?

24:13.583 --> 24:16.706
It can oil the wheels
after all.

24:16.708 --> 24:18.413
What do you think?

24:18.415 --> 24:21.248
- Mike in Barnet, hello.
- Hi, Jeff.

24:21.250 --> 24:23.706
Yeah, it sounds silly,
but we like... we like

24:23.708 --> 24:26.038
doing everything
together, whatever it is.

24:26.040 --> 24:28.538
Even if it is just getting a
Chinky on a Saturday night.

24:28.540 --> 24:30.538
Ooh, fried rice. Nice.

24:30.540 --> 24:33.623
We just love it, slobbing in
front of the telly. Perfect.

24:33.625 --> 24:35.581
Oh, thank you
for that, Mike.

24:35.583 --> 24:37.956
You mean a Chinese,
of course, don't you?

24:37.958 --> 24:40.788
Apologies
on Mike's behalf.

