26:06.790 --> 26:08.540
Bloody hell.

26:13.750 --> 26:14.833
I don't..

26:52.875 --> 26:53.873
Hello?

26:53.875 --> 26:55.456
Oh, Jesus!

26:55.458 --> 26:56.833
Oh.

26:59.208 --> 27:01.873
Marek? Marek?

27:01.875 --> 27:04.248
Pick up, please,
it's Tony.

27:04.250 --> 27:06.413
Hello, Tony.

27:06.415 --> 27:09.373
Listen, have you been over
here to this building?

27:09.375 --> 27:12.040
Mm, no.
I am in other one.

27:14.875 --> 27:18.081
I don't like
this place, Tony.

27:18.083 --> 27:21.416
It feels... bad.

27:22.665 --> 27:24.913
We have, um

27:24.915 --> 27:27.956
we have a word
for this back home.

27:27.958 --> 27:31.208
It is zloslivy.

27:34.665 --> 27:37.163
Look, don't, um..

27:37.165 --> 27:39.790
don't let them thoughts get
into your head, mate, alright?

27:41.665 --> 27:43.790
Get yourself a radio,
sunbeam. Yeah?

27:45.790 --> 27:48.456
Look, I'm gonna, uh,
take a walk around, right?

27:48.458 --> 27:49.873
You sit tight
for 10 minutes

27:49.875 --> 27:51.663
and I'll call you
when I get back, alright?

27:51.665 --> 27:54.663
Okay.
Thank you a lot, Tony.

27:54.665 --> 27:56.000
Alright, mate.

30:51.375 --> 30:52.790
Hello?

30:55.040 --> 30:56.625
Is anyone there?

31:08.915 --> 31:10.957
Marek? Marek?

31:13.790 --> 31:15.082
Dada?

31:17.415 --> 31:20.456
It is a coma.
A probable lock-in.

31:20.458 --> 31:22.623
He is here for keeps.

31:22.625 --> 31:23.998
Just one of those things.

31:24.000 --> 31:26.040
The lights are on
and nobody's home.

31:34.500 --> 31:35.956
Marek?

31:53.708 --> 31:55.081
Right, listen.

31:55.083 --> 31:57.038
You've got two minutes to
get out of this buildin'

31:57.040 --> 31:58.875
before I come for ya.

32:14.415 --> 32:16.457
Marek, if that's you..

32:20.333 --> 32:23.083
What.. I can't believe this.

33:13.125 --> 33:14.375
Hello?

33:25.958 --> 33:28.666
Oh, what the bloody..

33:31.165 --> 33:32.082
Oh.

33:41.708 --> 33:43.458
I'm not fuckin' about.

33:45.208 --> 33:48.083
Right. Yeah? Yeah?

34:11.791 --> 34:13.081
Shit.

34:20.873 --> 34:22.246
Dada.

34:27.333 --> 34:28.873
I'm comin' in.

34:57.916 --> 35:00.331
Yeah. I got you now.

35:09.291 --> 35:10.458
Yeah.

35:28.333 --> 35:30.583
Let me out! Let me out!

35:34.916 --> 35:36.083
Shit.

35:38.541 --> 35:39.958
What the..

35:56.291 --> 35:58.414
Dada!

36:23.458 --> 36:25.498
Do you know what brought
Tony back to the church?

36:25.500 --> 36:28.248
Uh, you know,
I am not comfortable

36:28.250 --> 36:31.373
talking so directly
about a parishioner.

36:31.375 --> 36:34.039
I'm assuming you have Tony's
permission to talk to me?

36:34.041 --> 36:35.498
Yeah, yeah, of course.

36:35.500 --> 36:37.164
But I can..

36:37.166 --> 36:39.831
I mean, I can ask you some
more indirect questions

36:39.833 --> 36:41.414
if you're comfortable
with that?

36:41.416 --> 36:43.664
- Yes.
- Okay. Great.

36:44.833 --> 36:47.833
Um, so..

36:50.000 --> 36:52.456
So what do you think
is your responsibility

36:52.458 --> 36:55.414
when a grown man like Tony
comes to you and says

36:55.416 --> 36:58.331
that they've had
a supernatural experience?

37:00.041 --> 37:03.164
You know, uh, when I was
a school's chaplain

37:03.166 --> 37:05.123
I would always say
to the boys

37:05.125 --> 37:07.331
"Age is not important
to the Lord.

37:07.333 --> 37:09.750
We are all children
before Him."

37:11.333 --> 37:13.498
If He wants you to believe

37:13.500 --> 37:15.914
He will send you a sign.

37:15.916 --> 37:19.039
That is what
these experiences are.

37:19.041 --> 37:20.373
Signs.

37:20.375 --> 37:22.414
Sure, but..

37:22.416 --> 37:24.456
Uh, Tony, with Tony, uh..

37:24.458 --> 37:27.748
Presumably, Tony told you
about his incident?

37:27.750 --> 37:29.789
Of course.

37:29.791 --> 37:32.789
The spirit.
The unquiet spirit.

37:32.791 --> 37:34.081
Yeah.

37:34.083 --> 37:35.331
So for a moment

37:35.333 --> 37:36.539
let's hypothesize that
that really happened...

37:36.541 --> 37:38.623
Oh, you do not need
to hypothesize.

37:38.625 --> 37:40.289
It did happen.

37:40.291 --> 37:42.748
Tony testifies
that he saw a spirit

37:42.750 --> 37:45.458
and he changed
his ways accordingly.

37:46.416 --> 37:48.373
But in what way
is that not real?

37:48.375 --> 37:52.039
Oh, of course, for Tony's
sighting to be taken seriously

37:52.041 --> 37:54.456
there's got to be some
sort of material evidence.

37:54.458 --> 37:57.831
Because without that,
it's, uh, you know..

37:57.833 --> 38:00.831
Tony has got so much
emotional baggage.

38:00.833 --> 38:03.666
Baggage? We... We are
talking about a man.

38:05.000 --> 38:06.416
Our brother.

38:09.083 --> 38:11.123
I'm so tired
of this modern disregard

38:11.125 --> 38:13.123
for the spiritual life.

38:13.125 --> 38:16.373
How unfashionable it's become
to believe in anything

38:16.375 --> 38:18.500
other than
our own personal gains.

38:20.291 --> 38:24.539
Did Tony tell you what he did
after he had that experience?

38:24.541 --> 38:25.706
No.

38:25.708 --> 38:28.331
He went to see his
daughter, Marnie, again

38:28.333 --> 38:30.914
the very next day.

38:30.916 --> 38:33.331
And when she heard
her father's voice

38:33.333 --> 38:36.581
for the first time
in five years

38:36.583 --> 38:39.456
the doctor said
her heart skipped a beat.

38:39.458 --> 38:43.123
That, I think, professor

38:43.125 --> 38:45.623
tells us everything
we need to know

38:45.625 --> 38:50.458
about the reality of that
experience and its value.

38:51.541 --> 38:53.623
You, Mr. Goodman,
would do well

38:53.625 --> 38:56.458
to think about that with
regard to your own family.

38:57.833 --> 38:59.875
Good day.

39:54.625 --> 39:55.623
Who is it?

39:55.625 --> 39:57.081
Uh, it's
Professor Philip Goodman.

39:57.083 --> 39:58.916
We spoke on the phone.

40:04.541 --> 40:07.539
Do you have an ID
or anything?

40:07.541 --> 40:10.123
You might not be the man
that I spoke to.

40:10.125 --> 40:11.581
I am.

40:15.833 --> 40:18.373
Oh, okay. Here you go.

40:18.375 --> 40:20.333
You sent that
to Charles Cameron.

40:32.125 --> 40:33.541
Come in.

40:41.916 --> 40:43.875
I'll be upstairs, mom.

41:06.500 --> 41:07.791
Professor Goodman?

41:54.666 --> 41:55.750
Simon?

42:17.291 --> 42:18.666
Simon?

42:41.750 --> 42:44.706
- Down here.
- Oh.

42:44.708 --> 42:46.000
Jesus.

42:52.750 --> 42:55.333
Demon.

42:56.416 --> 42:57.541
- Sit down.

43:02.708 --> 43:04.666
Please,
don't touch my books.

43:08.041 --> 43:09.748
God, it's boiling
in here, Simon.

43:09.750 --> 43:10.664
Oh, yeah, yeah, I know.

43:10.666 --> 43:11.664
I just get really cold

43:11.666 --> 43:12.831
and really uncomfortable

43:12.833 --> 43:14.873
so I just like it
to be as comfort..

43:14.875 --> 43:17.206
I just like it
how I like it.

43:25.125 --> 43:26.416
Wow.

43:28.041 --> 43:29.375
Uh, so..

43:30.833 --> 43:31.956
So what are all these..

43:31.958 --> 43:34.289
Where are
these pictures from?

43:34.291 --> 43:35.956
They're from...
They're from all over.

43:35.958 --> 43:37.789
It's my research.

43:37.791 --> 43:39.123
Stuff that I find
on the internet

43:39.125 --> 43:40.164
or books that I'm reading.

43:40.166 --> 43:42.373
Stuff I'm interested in.

43:42.375 --> 43:43.831
I'm just trying to
understand certain things.

43:43.833 --> 43:45.081
So it's helpful
to have all that stuff out

43:45.083 --> 43:46.623
so I can see it
all the time.

43:46.625 --> 43:47.873
Or at least
whenever I want to see it.

43:47.875 --> 43:50.248
If I don't wanna see it,
I can look over there.

43:50.250 --> 43:53.289
The thing
that I don't want..

43:53.291 --> 43:54.831
I don't want people
looking at me and thinking

43:54.833 --> 43:57.081
that I'm mad
'cause I know what I saw.

43:57.083 --> 43:58.914
And that's the thing.
I'm tired.

43:58.916 --> 44:00.873
I'm so tired
and I'm finding it hard

44:00.875 --> 44:01.998
to think straight right now.

44:02.000 --> 44:04.206
But, I mean,
I want to talk about this.

44:04.208 --> 44:05.289
I wanna find out
about this

44:05.291 --> 44:07.164
but I don't want
people to think..

44:07.166 --> 44:09.789
I just want everything
to be straight now.

44:09.791 --> 44:11.789
No frayed edges,
no loose ends.

44:11.791 --> 44:13.750
All straight. All smooth.

44:14.708 --> 44:15.875
I don't want..

44:18.208 --> 44:19.623
I don't want
people thinking that

44:19.625 --> 44:22.791
there's anything
wr... wrong with me.

44:26.375 --> 44:27.375
I see.

44:32.958 --> 44:34.000
You okay?

44:35.875 --> 44:36.791
Yeah.

44:40.791 --> 44:41.916
Okay.

44:43.416 --> 44:44.708
So..

44:46.000 --> 44:48.164
...who else is up here
with us

44:48.166 --> 44:51.039
in the...
in the upstairs room?

44:51.041 --> 44:52.206
No one. It's just us.

44:52.208 --> 44:53.581
No, sorry.
In the top bedroom?

44:53.583 --> 44:55.248
- My brother's old room.
- Right. Your brother.

44:55.250 --> 44:56.539
So is he still
living at home?

44:56.541 --> 44:58.164
Well, Mr. Perfect..

44:58.166 --> 45:01.623
No, he's 25 and married.
He's got a flat.

45:01.625 --> 45:03.583
There's no one here.
It's just us.

45:06.291 --> 45:07.623
- Sorry, I was just up...
- There's nobody here.

45:07.625 --> 45:08.956
I'm telling you
there's nobody here.

45:08.958 --> 45:10.916
Do you wanna go and look?

45:24.000 --> 45:26.166
- No.
- Fine then.

45:29.958 --> 45:32.583
Can you go away, please?
We're trying to talk.

45:39.708 --> 45:41.331
Do you not get on well
with your parents?

45:41.333 --> 45:43.291
They don't care about me.

45:45.291 --> 45:47.458
I know you're still there!

45:57.458 --> 45:59.625
Can you help me?

46:00.875 --> 46:02.875
I'll try.

46:07.750 --> 46:11.706
All I need you to do
is to just..

46:11.708 --> 46:13.914
...just tell me everything
you can about that night.

46:13.916 --> 46:15.956
Everything.

46:15.958 --> 46:18.039
If I can just understand
what happened

46:18.041 --> 46:20.166
then everything
will be fine.

46:25.750 --> 46:28.000
Okay.

46:30.791 --> 46:33.998
I'm not the same person
now as I was. It's..

46:34.000 --> 46:36.916
The world is
n... not the same.

46:38.250 --> 46:40.208
Oh, God.
I feel like such an idiot.

46:41.291 --> 46:42.666
Why?

46:48.666 --> 46:49.833
Yeah.

46:52.625 --> 46:54.583
I was driving
my dad's car.

46:55.583 --> 46:56.956
I failed my test

46:56.958 --> 46:59.125
but I was too afraid
to tell them.

47:00.958 --> 47:03.083
I pretended
that I had passed.

47:12.083 --> 47:14.208
I was driving
without a license.

47:51.958 --> 47:53.664
- Hello?
- Where are you?

47:53.666 --> 47:55.539
I'm in the car. I am on the
way back from the party.

47:55.541 --> 47:57.039
Oh, thank God.

47:57.041 --> 47:59.039
He's in the car, Raymond.

47:59.041 --> 48:01.164
We've been trying to call you.
Where have you been?

48:01.166 --> 48:03.123
I... I'm sorry. There's no
reception near Eddie's.

48:03.125 --> 48:05.123
We've been sitting here
on shpilkes.

48:05.125 --> 48:06.789
You should have been
back hours ago.

48:06.791 --> 48:08.289
Should have been back
hours ago!

48:08.291 --> 48:11.123
Oh, Raymond, for God's
sake, I'm trying to talk..

48:11.125 --> 48:12.083
Hello?

48:27.333 --> 48:28.373
Hello?

48:28.375 --> 48:29.748
Your mother's
gone to bed.

48:29.750 --> 48:31.123
We are very upset.

48:31.125 --> 48:33.081
Dad, I didn't put
the phone down on you.

48:33.083 --> 48:34.081
Oh.

48:34.083 --> 48:36.039
And I'm sorry
that I'm late.

48:36.041 --> 48:38.414
I just found that bloody
housing form for university

48:38.416 --> 48:40.123
that you should have
sent in three weeks ago.

48:40.125 --> 48:41.581
You told me
you'd sent it!

48:41.583 --> 48:44.123
Well, I... I thought...
I thought that I had.

48:44.125 --> 48:46.164
You're a bloody liar,
Simon.

48:46.166 --> 48:47.456
You're a liar.

48:47.458 --> 48:49.039
You might be able
to schmooze your mother

48:49.041 --> 48:50.789
but you cannot
schmooze me.

48:50.791 --> 48:52.414
You lied about that form.

48:52.416 --> 48:54.498
You lied about getting that
Saturday job, didn't you?

48:54.500 --> 48:56.206
What are we gonna
find out next?

48:56.208 --> 48:57.914
That you lied about passing
your driving test?

48:57.916 --> 48:59.206
- Shit.
- I'll tell you what.

48:59.208 --> 49:01.166
I'm sick
to the bloody back teeth.

49:03.375 --> 49:04.916
Shit.

49:16.208 --> 49:18.581
Don't you put the bloody
phone down on me!

49:18.583 --> 49:20.164
I... I... I didn't put
the phone down on you.

49:24.000 --> 49:25.289
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

49:25.291 --> 49:27.164
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Oh, my..

49:27.166 --> 49:29.333
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

49:40.875 --> 49:42.208
You okay?

49:54.166 --> 49:55.916
Oh, my God.

50:39.000 --> 50:42.750
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

51:11.875 --> 51:13.083
No signal.

51:31.500 --> 51:33.125
Come on.

52:14.208 --> 52:16.166
Fucking O2.

52:28.208 --> 52:30.414
- Hello? National Breakdown.
- Hello.

52:30.416 --> 52:32.625
Can you give me the car's
registration, please?

52:35.125 --> 52:36.666
Just give me one second.

52:39.291 --> 52:43.458
AG57-EOZ.

52:45.500 --> 52:48.373
Thank you.
And is that Mr. Rif-kind?

52:48.375 --> 52:50.664
Rifkind. Yes.

52:50.666 --> 52:52.539
I'm Simon. I'm his son.

52:52.541 --> 52:53.789
Okay, Simon.

52:53.791 --> 52:55.831
And are you with the car
right now?

53:00.416 --> 53:02.208
Hello, Simon?

53:04.125 --> 53:05.914
Yes.

53:05.916 --> 53:07.331
Yes, I'm right by the car.

53:07.333 --> 53:09.539
Okay,
we have you on the GPS

53:09.541 --> 53:12.373
so we know exactly where you
are and we'll be with you

53:12.375 --> 53:15.914
somewhere between 10
and 45 minutes, okay?

53:15.916 --> 53:18.623
Please come
as quickly as you can.

53:18.625 --> 53:20.831
Thank you, Mr. Rif-kind.
Goodbye.

53:20.833 --> 53:22.208
Rifkind!

53:41.166 --> 53:43.414
What have I done?
What have I done?

54:15.416 --> 54:16.625
Hello?

54:47.000 --> 54:49.958
God, I'm... I'm so sorry.

54:56.416 --> 54:59.791
- Stay!
- Fuck that!

56:09.625 --> 56:13.208
The supernatural are unseen
forces that surround us.

56:31.708 --> 56:34.706
Charles,
I've now investigated

56:34.708 --> 56:36.875
two of your cases
quite thoroughly.

56:38.708 --> 56:41.206
It feels quite simple
to me, really.

56:41.208 --> 56:42.664
The brain sees
what it wants to see.

56:42.666 --> 56:44.873
They're your words,
Charles.

56:44.875 --> 56:46.498
Tony Matthews
is an alcoholic

56:46.500 --> 56:48.331
who's wrestling
with unresolved grief.

56:48.333 --> 56:51.706
And Simon
is a fragile young man

56:51.708 --> 56:54.706
and from a deeply
dysfunctional family

56:54.708 --> 56:56.206
who's on the edge
of psychosis.

57:06.500 --> 57:08.998
I understand
all too well, Charles

57:09.000 --> 57:11.414
how easy it is
to get confused

57:11.416 --> 57:14.664
and to lose faith
in one's own judgment.

57:14.666 --> 57:18.458
Especially when we're
tired and emotional..

57:21.791 --> 57:23.583
...and unwell.

57:49.916 --> 57:51.081
What the..

57:56.791 --> 57:58.706
Keep up, Goodman.

57:58.708 --> 58:01.498
Thing is, I'm the soppy one
if you can believe that.

58:01.500 --> 58:03.456
I wanted kids from the
moment we got together

58:03.458 --> 58:05.123
but Maria said, "No, it's
not gonna happen, babe."

58:05.125 --> 58:06.123
Maria is your wife, yeah?

58:06.125 --> 58:07.289
Yeah, of course, she is.

58:07.291 --> 58:08.664
Do you know why
she didn't want children?

58:08.666 --> 58:10.998
Presumably, you were
comfortable financially.

58:11.000 --> 58:12.623
Oh, Jesus.

58:12.625 --> 58:15.539
That's all your lot ever think
about, isn't it? Money.

58:15.541 --> 58:17.581
Sorry, what exactly
do you mean by your lot?

58:17.583 --> 58:18.748
No way
was she getting pregnant

58:18.750 --> 58:20.706
until she was made
a partner at the firm.

58:20.708 --> 58:22.331
Her words, not mine.

58:22.333 --> 58:23.789
Priorities.

58:23.791 --> 58:24.873
Someone's got to earn
the money

58:24.875 --> 58:26.664
so you brainy poofters
can sit around

58:26.666 --> 58:28.414
stroking your chins
and pulling onion

58:28.416 --> 58:29.789
out of your arses
all day long.

58:29.791 --> 58:32.289
Oh, hang on.

58:32.291 --> 58:34.164
Yeah, I've got to do this.

58:34.166 --> 58:36.123
Right.

58:52.083 --> 58:53.581
Alright.

58:53.583 --> 58:55.498
Can we, please,
talk about the incident?

58:55.500 --> 58:57.206
Do you know what they used to
call me when I was trading?

58:57.208 --> 58:58.373
- No.
- The prophet.

58:58.375 --> 58:59.914
I had a sixth sense
of what was going up

58:59.916 --> 59:01.831
and what was coming down.

59:01.833 --> 59:03.623
This isn't about
the financial markets.

59:03.625 --> 59:06.666
I know what it is
you're asking about.

59:10.666 --> 59:11.791
I know.

59:14.125 --> 59:16.000
Come on then, up there.

59:21.625 --> 59:23.914
I made a killing
in the city.

59:23.916 --> 59:27.081
Uh, I built the house.
Real investment property.

59:27.083 --> 59:29.831
And that's where the incident
happened, at the house?

59:29.833 --> 59:32.456
When Maria
finally got partnership

59:32.458 --> 59:34.956
bingo,
time to have a baby.

59:34.958 --> 59:37.664
But she was pushing 40
when we started though.

